<inglise> Council Regulation (EC) No 2611/95 of 25 October 1995 establishing the possibility of national aid being granted in compensation for losses of agricultural income caused by monetary movements in other Member States </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2611/95, millega kehtestatakse riikliku abi andmise v&otilde;imalus saamata j&auml;&auml;nud p&otilde;llumajandusliku tulu h&uuml;vitamiseks teistes liikmesriikides toimunud valuutakursside k&otilde;ikumiste t&otilde;ttu 25. oktoober 1995 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Articles 42 and 43 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikleid 42 ja 43, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas monetary movements have influenced the agricultural market particularly in the first half of 1995; whereas certain producers may have suffered from losses of income caused by significant monetary movements in Member States other than the one in which they produce; </inglise>
<eesti> valuutakursside k&otilde;ikumised on m&otilde;jutanud p&otilde;llumajandusturgu eelk&otilde;ige 1995. aasta esimesel poolel; teatavatel tootjatel on v&otilde;inud j&auml;&auml;da saamata tulu m&auml;rgatavate valuutak&otilde;ikumiste t&otilde;ttu muudes liikmesriikides kui see, kus nad toodavad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, where such losses of income are objectively established, temporary national aid which does not favour a particular type of production may be granted to compensate for the loss actually established; whereas it is necessary for the Community to take measures to enable the common agricultural policy to be coherently implemented; </inglise>
<eesti> kui selline saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu on objektiivselt kindlaks tehtud, v&otilde;ib tegelikult kindlakstehtud saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulude h&uuml;vitamiseks anda ajutist riiklikku abi, mille puhul ei eelistata konkreetset tooteliiki; &uuml;hendus peab v&otilde;tma meetmeid &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika j&auml;rjekindla rakendamise tagamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these exceptional measures are justified solely on the basis of the specific objectives, circumstances and features of the common agricultural policy, </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused erakorralised meetmed on &otilde;igustatud &uuml;ksnes &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika konkreetsetest eesm&auml;rkidest, asjaoludest ja ise&auml;rasustest tulenevatel kaalutlustel, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Where it can be justified on the basis of facts that agricultural producers of given production sectors have suffered considerable losses of revenue in a Member State because of significant monetary movements which have occured in other Member States since the beginning of the 1994/95 marketing year and no later than 31 December 1995, flat-rate compensatory aid, reducing over three years, may be granted to the producers in question on the basis of national financing. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui faktide abil on v&otilde;imalik tuvastada, et teatavate tootmissektorite p&otilde;llumajandustootjatel on j&auml;&auml;nud saamata m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rne eelarvetulu teistes liikmesriikides alates 1994/95. turustusaasta algusest ja hiljemalt 31. detsembril 1995 toimunud valuutakursside k&otilde;ikumiste t&otilde;ttu, v&otilde;ib k&otilde;nealustele tootjatele kolme aasta jooksul maksta kindla suurusega j&auml;rkj&auml;rguliselt v&auml;henevat tasandustoetust riikliku rahastamise alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> The compensatory aid shall at the most be equal to the aforementioned loss of income and may not be granted in the form of an amount linked to production other than that of a fixed period corresponding to that in which the income was lost. </inglise>
<eesti> Tasandustoetuse summa v&otilde;rdub maksimaalselt eespool nimetatud saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tuluga ning seda ei v&otilde;i toodanguga seoses maksta muu kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajavahemiku eest kui see, mil k&otilde;nealune tulu on saamata j&auml;&auml;nud. </eesti>
<inglise> It may not be so directed as to favour a particular type of production in the sector concerned nor be dependent on production subsequent to that fixed period. </inglise>
<eesti> Toetuse maksmisel ei v&otilde;i eelistada asjaomase sektori kindlat tooteliiki ning see ei v&otilde;i s&otilde;ltuda p&auml;rast k&otilde;nealust kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajavahemikku valmistatud toodangust. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall determine the amounts and detailed rules of this aid and notify them to the Commission for approval. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid m&auml;&auml;ravad k&otilde;nealuse abi summad ja maksmise &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad ning edastavad need komisjonile kinnitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> The procedural provisions of Article 93 of the Treaty shall apply without taking account of the criteria in Article 92. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatakse asutamislepingu artikli 93 menetluss&auml;tteid, v&otilde;tmata arvesse artikli 92 kriteeriume. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> If, during the three-year period in which aid may be granted, a trend in prices due to monetary movements is recorded before the second or third annual tranche is paid, which offsets the losses on which the aid was based, the Commission shall decide, after consulting the Member State concerned, to reduce appropriately or abolish the remaining tranches. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nende kolme aasta jooksul, mil abi v&otilde;ib anda, registreeritakse enne teise v&otilde;i kolmanda osamakse tegemist valuutakursside k&otilde;ikumiste t&otilde;ttu hinnasuundumus, mis h&uuml;vitab abi andmisel aluseks olnud saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu, otsustab komisjon p&auml;rast asjaomase liikmesriigiga konsulteerimist, kas j&auml;relej&auml;&auml;nud osamakseid asjakohaselt v&auml;hendada v&otilde;i need t&uuml;histada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> A Member State may not notify an aid project under this Regulation after 30 June 1996. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik ei v&otilde;i teatada k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega h&otilde;lmatud abiprojektist p&auml;rast 30. juunit 1996. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Luxembourg, 25. oktoober 1995 N&otilde;ukogu nimel </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 25 October 1995. </inglise>
<eesti> eesistuja L. ATIENZA SERNA </eesti>
